A must have in this area. Finally healthy fast food. And vegan/vegetarian options too. Friendly service and the salads are tasty too. Macros and other detailed nutritional information is available online too. Really great full for this option.
Thank you for vegan options!
Placed order for take out and my order was all wrong so disappointed if this location.

Went to this restaurant, first time and we had a wonderful experience. The ambiance was great. The decor on the walls and ceiling are classics (Cadillac, motorcycles and a plane-so cool). The food was very good. The waitress Paula was very professional and waited on us on a timely manner and was attentive. The staff was very friendly and we were also greeted by the manager Mercedes, she was amicable and was happy to hear that we enjoyed our experience.
Man the servers made us feel right at home. Music was excellent had everyone dancing. The food was so good very good portions even better as leftovers. The drinks were perfect!
Just the best
The food is good and the people who work there are really nice and polite. It's my go to when I don't cook.
Pizza is amazing wings are delicious great customer service

Came here from a recommendation from locals and this was a great choice. Everything was delicious here!  Ordered the Couyon Daddy and it was very flavourful, honestly could have shared this one with someone , portion was great. My friend ordered the Mushroom Soft Scramble and the potatoes were seasoned so well , I crave for it. You got to go early, because seating is limited in doors and fills out really quickly.

Walked in without reservation on Saturday night and they were able to seat us within 20mins. Food is delicious with tons of veg and non-veg options. Cocktails were really good - the pho infused gin cocktail was my favorite
Service is a bit odd, our server was amazing but when food came around it seemed like any staff at the restaurant could grab it and almost dump it on the table. Bit of an odd contrast.
Great service, great food, fast service, and great vibe.
Not very organized in their que, but it is what it is.
Rib tips tasted like oil didnâ€™t have any other flavor, the seasoned rice stuff was dry, the baked chicken leg quarter didnâ€™t have any seasoning it just tasted bland wasted money last night.
thats a great
I've been eating at these restaurants for decades (multiple locations), great food, great service, and reasonably priced. Recommend!
NOT ONLY IS THE FOOD GOOD BUT THE WORKERS HAVE SUCH A PLEASANT PERSONALITY. AND PLEASE TRY THE POUND CAKES OMG...YOU WANT BE DISAPPOINTED.
Honestly horrible. There were two feathers with my chicken wings . Deep fried to all hell. Sliders were ok. Mediocre at best

Food is amazing but the service..oh Lord!!!! On three different occasions, I ordered over the phone, they confirmed order received and drove 40mins to the restaurant only to be told what I ordered isnâ€™t available. It just happened today as well resulting in this review. Please fix this cos we love yall
This place is lit. Good price and portions, bring cash or be ready to venmo

Iâ€™ve ordered our Chinese new year dinners from this restaurant for years and our friends and family rave about the food. The restaurant is family run and super friendly. I highly recommend the beef chow fun, whole steamed sea bass with ginger and scallion, Peking duck, dry braised string beans, mu shu chicken. They also have a sticky rice stuffed chicken dish that is famous (on my list to try). Order the steamed sea bass and sticky rice stuffed chicken dish 24 hours in advance.

The owners were there every time I went. Very friendly atmosphere where I could tell it was full of regular customers.  Their open Monday through Fri from 10 to 2. Great local place to have local food. I've eaten in the restaurant and had take out. On Friday they have a seafood platter with shrimp creole.  The shrimp creole is great.
I love the fact that there is two Chick-fil-A around the corner from each other no waiting..

I happened upon Pluck by chance while looking to book myself a Singles Awareness Day dinner while I was on vacation. It sounded intriguing, so I took a chance. I was not disappointed! The food was amazing, from appetizers to entrees to dessert. But the real show stopper is the bottled wine list. Well, really hard to call a small novela a "list." Pretty much anything you could want in terms of variety was there, with recommendations from the staff. I also have to mention the atmosphere...great decor with a pretty great playlist for background. Next time I visit New Orleans, I'll be back!
Food is always on point. From breakfast to dinner.
Great Taco For Low Price

The food is great but the price tags are not clear. You can't rely on the display to plan your budget. The guy that served was impatient and seemed too much in a hurry. But, a very nice lady took over and concluded the transaction. Nice ambience, clean restaurant. Only problem was the guy at the counter, otherwise a really great place.
Very noisy place
Great place for great fried chicken and catfish.
Karime and her team always working moving fast everytime I go inside to eat she is always kind n I really appreciate the service.

"OMG! This is beyond adorable!  Cutest thing I've seen all day! "
"Wow, what a stunning dog!  The epitome of grace and beauty! "Your home and these dreamy puppies are a match made in heaven!  I'm totally in love with this picture! "
Great food & atmosphere

WOW! What an amazing experience we had today at KenCooks. Great food, greeted by a wonderful hostess. Felt like home. Food was fresh, hot, didn't take forever. My favorite dishes were the Yams, and the fried salmon. The plates were plentiful and priced just right. The next time I'm in Charlotte.  I will be there. Theres a lot of love and care going on in this kitchen. Thank you so much!
Fusion Caribbean Kitchen replaced another Jamaican restaurant. I'm a rice girl and LOVE that they ALWAYS have an assortment. Servers are cordial and efficient. Affordable prices.
We had a great lunch yesterday for gathering.  Nice food and environment.
Muy casero

The first time I went I had to ask the lady to change my dirty fork. Then, the second time I had something floating in my coffee. I tried to get the ladyâ€™s attention to change it, but she was too busy chatting away. Food is ok.

We are so glad we did not bother with the jacket nonsense.  I told my husband not to bother. We had the BEST experience today. We had 5:30 reservations.  We were taken through a large area. We went to a nice area. We greeted by Andrew, he was very nice and made sure we were taken care of. Our server was Brittney, what an excellent server and so-so nice. Brittney made sure all was perfect.  Ask for Brittney. Good luck to you Brittney.   Our souffle potatoes OMG! Filet mignon cooked perfectly.  The cauliflower a little undercooked. All went well.  Will come back for sure.

Why didn't anyone tell me we had a Korean fried chicken spot in Fort Worth? I came here for lunch to check it out and they had so many options. The cashier was very patient and helpful while I was deciding what's for lunch. Her recommendation was fire. Now I know where to go when I want Korean fried chicken.
10/10 service but the food was pretty boring. We had the catfish platter and muffuletta poboy. Bother were pretty bland and unexciting.

I ordered pizza from this company all the time and today I received my pizza. The pizza was burnt, taste like a burnt pizza and absolutely hard as a rock felt like a paper weight. I called at 8:17pm on 10/22 to let them know and person I spoke to was absolutely condescending and rude. Explain to me that I was wrong and this is how it is made. I reiterated that I order all the time and this is not how their pizza taste. It taste like burnt cardboard. He then says this is how we make it and hangs up phone. I will never order again just off customer service. If they acknowledged their mistake and even offered to remake then I wouldnâ€™t be writing this review and would continue to be a loyal customer.

Dined in on 4/30/2022.

The food was decent, but they DON'T offer tap water. How do you charge $2 for bottled water in Flushing? Unacceptable.

A group of diners sitting to our right ordered bottled waters halfway during their meal because their throats were parched. The family sitting in front of us left several disposable plastic cups and opened bottled waters. All the diners there were pushed to order bottled water. How do you finish the meal otherwise?

Worst customer service, non stop talking over the food, all the food open no cover, man who was serving rude on 4/14/2024 Sunday  terrible service. Food isnâ€™t bad, the worker needs customer service training. No going back there to eat.

Just had Nopalitos at the Spiritas Ranch Subdivision grand opening. This was my first time to try them and I was not disappointed. Everything was so flavorful and the food was fresh and hot. Service was impeccable. Whenever Iâ€™m in the Fort Worth area, I am definitely going to stop at their restaurant and sit in to have a meal. I highly recommend them!
I'm a big fan. The short ribs were delicious. The guacamole is made right in front of you. The drinks were good. 5 stars

Sat down with large party at 6:30pm, all recieved meals by 7:15, mine showed up at 7:30- not what I ordered, next try 7:45  came back with something I did not order. All my party are ready to leave and I need now to wait till 8 for.meal. Decided to leave and go across the street to get a burger.

Quite frankly, all seemed intentional

Do not recommend it!
horrible service
The corn chowder and garlicky roll were divine.
Excellent Al Pastor tacos here. Cabeza was good too, but carnitas was under seasoned for me.

Tried before seeing reviews. Burger itself was fine, just very bland. Constructed very messy too the point where when I u wrapped it my top bun was next to my burger. Not cold but also for $20 (burger and fountain drink) honestly McDonald's is 10 times better. Wouldn't go back
Food and service was excellent.
This is a special place for high quality herbs and food at a reasonable price. The decor is cool and comfortable. The service is friendly. Love to be here and will try more dishes in the near future.

I don't really ever leave reviews but Baba's Eats deserves the recognition and the 5 star review. I got the chicken schwarma and tacos and it was amazing at a very reasonable price. I highly recommend stopping here for food, snacks, or drinks if you are ever in the area
Sit at the bar and watch Love - heâ€™s amazing! Fresh oysters and hurricanes - yes please!

The food and service here is excellent!  Waiter was very busy but kept us up to date on our food coming out, was very nice, and we always had drinks.  Come at happy hour and prices for a lot of good dishes are discounted.  Atmosphere is nice, lots of good music playing.  Everything we had was very good, especially the oysters, definitely stop in!
I got sick and they acted liked they could not hear what I said
Iâ€™ve been eating here since they opened up , and let me be the 1st to say , this spot hasnâ€™t failed me once , and theyâ€™re clutch .REAL LATE NIGHT  Soul food at
Bad bad bad all bad donâ€™t eat here

Where to even beginning I was so excited when I found out Henryâ€™s majestic was back in business!! The service to the atmosphere of this place is amazing the food so delicious my go to is the calamari and Cuban cigars the drinks are all strong and delicious my go to is the majestic swizzle fun and colorful if you havenâ€™t been you are missing out!!
Pho ga taste good and perfect for office. Im so glad i give this place a try.

Sat at the bar and chatted a lovely bar tender who offered me advice on local attractions. This was nice as I was traveling alone. Food was great and nice spicy Margâ€™s. Iâ€™ll be back when I return later in the year.
Excellent food and the owner was very nice/personable. A definite must visit if you are in the area.

Best beef on weck outside of Buffalo!  I go to Andersons when I am home but Lebowski has the best beef on weck locally.  We will return!  I ordered the sampler as I was craving wings & beer battered haddock too.  My husband ordered 3 sliders, he enjoyed his burgers & beef on weck.
rude staff
Complete trash ruined my drive order tried to call number dont work went up there no so called sandwich artist around complete trash service
This location uses credit card skimmers, do not stop at this Shell.

We went to the location just outside of Midway. Really cool inside with good parking. Our server was wonderful. Their Italian chopped salad was great, and we had a deep dish pizza. I prefer a NY style, but am glad to have tried it.

I really dislike patronizing my own people establishments. OMG. It took 20 minutes for someone to come and take my order. Then when she did, she didn't write it down and of course my order was incorrect. Cmon people get it right. Then you wonder why we have negativity towards us. Just get it right it's not that hard. Lastly my darn chicken came out so dark because if old bad grease and it tasted that way that I couldn't eat it. Everything I travel to NC I always try to make this my goto but now I'm startng to second guess. I know I will never revisit the Durham location. Cmon BRUHS. Let's get it back on track.

My first time and I must say I enjoyed! The seafood platter for $15 was a win. The food taste fresh and the sauce was very good. I will see them in the future on Fridays for sure. This is a local gem that we should support! Plus the food is really good!
Best cheesesteak around town. It is worth detouring around Cheshire bridges closure to get these tasty sandwiches

The lady who picks up the phone in the morning has a disgusting attitude, doesnâ€™t let you finish a sentence and immediately dismisses what you have to say. If you hate your job, donâ€™t work there, simple, but she had an attitude as soon as she picked up the phone, if I call a restaurant I am PAYING for food, I expect to be received with a welcoming tone, especially at 8am in the morning.

I've been obsessed with Planta ever since my first visit but this location surprised me in all the wrong ways. It's different than all the other Planta locations in that the customer service is garbage. They treat you like it's a burden for them to serve you. They asked us where we would like to sit and we chose outside seating. 10, 15, 20 minutes go by and no server comes to get our orders (restaurant was not busy and severs were inside chatting). Almost half an hour later a lady comes out to tell us that "the servers don't want to come outside bc they've pollen allergies"... after finishing our lunch inside we come out only to find out that there are multiple parties sitting outside and getting served, even have a photo as a proof. The same server who denied to come outside to serve us was the one serving others when we left. I've never been treated so badly at any restaurant let alone a Planta. The bathroom had a weird smell and wasnâ€™t clean. Management seemed whack as we had multiple different servers serving and randomly coming to our table. Mainly, it felt like we didnâ€™t belong there and felt like we were facing racism. I am so so unhappy and disappointed.
Service was not organized and had no clue what they are doing, ordered food but at the end no food was cooked and delivered to the table. Finally we left the restaurant!

This was a very nice restaurant, The atmosphere was great.
The food was good

The RIBS were bussin and the TIPS had that char to it damn its good the chili dogs was ok the beans and mac is good to now the potatoes salad is different from what we like down here and it had onions in it to but besides that they cook different stuff to I heard the turkey legs and oxtails is  the truth but the food was good and the Customer Service was good too
This is the only place I eat at. Most immaculate Chinese food I've had in my life.
Napa on Providence offers excellent service and fresh, locally-sourced contemporary American dishes, showcasing their dedication to quality.
The soup was terrible more rice than broth chicken wings was dry

Wonderful little restaurant and bar in the French Quarter of New Orleans. The oysters were so big and fresh I had to cut them in 1/2 to fit on a cracker! True story! Great atmosphere and a friendly staff. Prices were fair for a tourist town. Alligator taxidermy was a plus! Gator Man Approved
The food is good, the owner needs to get his staff more help. Twice Iâ€™ve waited over 30 minutes for food.
Rated 1 because of inaccurate hours. Reply to this review when they've been updated properly and I'll happily replace with 5 star rating. Until then, beware, dishonest business hours advertised here
Excellent NY pizza. Friendly place. And there's seating in the back.
Very nice waffle house location. Staffs are friendly and helpful. Foods are as expected. Parking is very convenient on site. Location is the best in Buckhead.

Nothing on here said they are only doing take out.  Went out of our way and didn't realize they were closed for inside dining until we got to the door.  We were nervous when there weren't many cars in parking lot
Being that this restaurant is on Bourbon, I figured the food would just be okay. I was pleasantly surprised how good the food actually was.

Food Was Hot And Delicious,Karaoke Was Nice and Fun But Service Not Good The Girl never asked if we were ok our first time there Customer Service needs to be Better I Asked About Special she wasnt even sure she was gonna check and never came back to tell me anything so Ordered what I ordered and PiÅ„a Colada wasn't frozen it was Very Liquidy.

This was a good experience, randomly walk in here and sat at the bar, the bartender was very attentive with me. I ordered a MEZCALITA  and it was very tasty and  mild. I wasnâ€™t too hungry so I try the loaded fries and I really enjoyed it. Over all I was pleased with my experience here, for sure Iâ€™m coming back with my folks for a good Wednesday dinner.

Seriously good chicken! We tried fried chicken, poutine with chicken, and the cauliflower; all are a must!  Some of the best fried chicken you may ever have in your life. The seasonings added onto the chicken makes this a flavor bomb and different from all others. Juicy all the way through too!

Superb service and a fun atmosphere.

Very limited seating. We got lucky and showed up early during a weekday and got last open table.
Very good very passionate staff and the food is just right on point

The service was not good at all. I understand its a haitian restaurant but u have to have the ability to speak and understand english. Or am i asking for too much??? Not all customers are haitian or speak creole.. or is that all they wanna serve?
Best fresh pasta and bread

their side orders are overpriced. The cost is the same as an actual plate of food. 26.29 for 2 sides (fried pork & smothered veggies no meat) ridiculous. I have never gotten food from here before and my first time is my last. On a scale of 1-10 the sides where a 5.  I did take out but if you are going to dine in then just know the music is loud.
Always a great vibe going in there
This place sucks! The service is horrible. The wait is too long. Unprofessional.
Have eaten here twice now and it is honestly some of the best food I have ever had. Best Indian restaurant in the city hands down. Get the cauliflower.
Speaks no English and will get mad at you for not being able to speak English even tho the entire menu and payment options are in Englishâ€¦. Will never return

The staff at this restaurant is completely unprofessional.
The customer service is horrible.
Not sure how clean they are either, I have serious doubts

Hippoke hits the spot every time!
Big portion, packed nicely, taste great!
And I can just tell there are some really sweet people behind the food!
Love the food there large subs as big as long breads, food is tasteful My favorite is steak and cheese never go wrong with this place..
Ask for Pamela, she's great!
Antoine was OUTSTANDING!! Customer service was perfectâ€¦ definitely will be back!
Always fresh a friendly staff

I had the carne asada quesadilla w/ sour cream and guacamole, my wife ordered the pozole and we shared buffalo wings. I had a $4.50 jarritos ( just a tad bit expensive) and the missus, water. The cost was about $54, which, in San Francisco is about average. The dinner was amazingly tasty and I would recommend this little joint any day.
Worst fried rice I've ever tasted, it was black. The noodles on my other dish were so soft they tasted like mush. I will never return.
Horrible place, customer service sucks , will never go to this place again
It was really good I would sell a toe for the food again!!!
Best chicken tenders and smoothie ever.

Alright, my expectations are pretty low because Iâ€™m grabbing a meal in a busy airport. BUT! I was pleasantly surprised by Urban Olive.

1. Super fast - like they had my meal out in seconds and it was fresh off the grill.
2. So friendly. Actually. Iâ€™ve never had a friendly experience at an airport restaurant. Kudos to the staff.
3. Relatively healthy. Itâ€™s nice to have veggies and protein to fill up on before a long flight.
4. Surprisingly affordable. I would have expected to pay this for a quick-serve restaurant in the real world, and I didnâ€™t feel price gouged.
5. The renovations in Terminal 5 are fresh and modern (finally) and make it a nice atmosphere for people watching and relaxing for a few minutes during a travel day.

All in all, pleased

Amazing food. Josiah took care of us and he was incredibly pleasant and helpful. I hade the shrimp poboy with fries and both were absolutely delicious. The atmosphere definitely made the experience memorable. I want to go back soon!

Cafeteria style quick and easy breakfast and sandwiches. Butternut/apple soup was very good.

Close to Metro
Very nice

We held our daughterâ€™s baby shower at Tribeca. Ashely was so easy to work with and all of our expectations were exceeded. It was a beautiful venue and the food was delicious! We received so many compliments and positive comments from our guests. We would highly recommend Tribeca for any private events you would like to hold.
Customer service was very poorly, I donâ€™t know the Hispanic manager name, because she didnâ€™t have on a name tag. I will never  order from this Chick-fil-A again!!!!!!! Very rude.

Very unprofessional group of employees,band a useless manager. I waited 30 minutes inside the restaurant for my food after waiting in drive thru for 15 minutes for 2 Biggie combos. Stay away from this one.
Very good lamb burger. The waitress was friendly.
The Salted Pearl is absolutely phenomenal. The Crabmeat Au Gratin is divine, oyster happy hour is great and their lobster mac and cheese is one of the best in the city.
Great brunch spot that also serves alcohol. Liquor dispenser just renewed. Cozy spot.
Itâ€™s always a vibe good food good drinks.
Prices can be better
I ordered online through Uber eats. I got the chicken gyro and it was amazing I got it with rice and a Greek salad. 10/10 my new go to
This place our favorite for eat a delicious pizza

The best Dominican food! This is by far the best Dominican food in town. Love coming here for my lunch break. I feel at home. From the owners to the serves they are all so welcoming and friendly. I would recommend this place for those looking for a true Dominican style breakfast, lunch or dinner.
Got judged for asking for guacamole and then they forgot to add guacamole ðŸ¤¡
I had hair in my rice

Napoli has quickly become my favorite take out spotin the East. The customer service is always great and the food is consistently amazing! I love patronizing local businesses and Napoli makes the choice easy because theyâ€™re friendly and always handle the food and customers with care and kindness!
This was a great place with an extensive menu and awesome service
My food was amazing juice is also a 10/10 . Our server was great!

OMG I think I have found the best tostones I've ever had in my life! Fresh, piping hot, crispy on the outside, light a fluffy inside. Also had their empanadas which were stuffed to the max and perfectly fried. I didn't try it but I love their idea of rice bowls for a Domincan spot. I haven't seen that except with Asian food so props to Las Palmas for the creativity. I have had their food for a catered event too and nothing was left!   We  all knew it was good. Clean, fair priced, I could go on. I WILL be back!!

Update 4/20/24
They completely changed their menu or chef. Food tastes great now. Glad to see the bartenders are still the same. Great drinks, great vibes.

I love the rooftop view. Food isnâ€™t all that great, takes forever to come to your table. If youâ€™re here for drinks and a good time with friendsâ€”you wonâ€™t be disappointed. If youâ€™re here for food, I suggest you book elsewhere unless youâ€™re gonna order 6 plates of their garlic shrimp.

Do not order this for delivery. We stayed .3 miles away. After 1 hour called and they said 30 more min. This was at 4:30 pm. Worst pizza and garlic cheese bread I've ever ate and I'm 47 years old. Do not call this place for delivery.

I love them specially at 2 am after club lol going there and get $20 tenders with fries omggg you will never regret when you have your "pollitos" in your hand with blue cheese and ketchup on the side please anf thank you jaja
Food is great!

I only got an iced tea but the barista was so friendly and welcoming.  I would love to come back for the food.  It looked very good with reasonable prices.  Recommend for those looking for a local vibe

This restaurant is definitely overhyped in New Orleans. Securing a reservation can be tough, which might give you the impression that everyone is clamoring to dine at Galatoire's. They enforce a formal dress code, and if you arrive without a jacket, they'll provide you with one if you want to sit in the main dining area. You'll quickly notice that the clientele tends to be on the older side.
Once you're seated and handed the menu, the waiters are quite focused on upselling you on various items. We opted for a crab salad to start, and honestly, it was presented in the most disappointing manner I've ever seen from a high-end restaurant. Our main courses, shrimp creole and crab sardou with spinach and artichoke, also lacked in presentation. While the taste was decent, it fell short of gourmet standards, especially given the price.
Service wasn't particularly efficient either; we observed waiters wandering around aimlessly. I'm not trying to criticize the place unfairly, but I truly don't believe it deserves to be ranked among the city's top restaurants. If you adjust your expectations accordingly, you may be able to avoid disappointment.

Super disappointed. We, a party of 2, had a brunch reservation for 12pm today. We checked in a little early, and the hostess let us know the kitchen was running behind by 40 minutes and that the wait would not be longer than 40 minutes. We said no problem, weâ€™ll wait at the bar. Checked in at the 45 minute mark and table was not ready. Itâ€™s now almost an hour and a half later and our table is still not ready. We left 30 minutes ago.

This seems like a perpetual issue based on reviews so would love to see management make some changes. Weâ€™ll try again another day, and will update my review then.
The service was great and friendly. The food was hot and delicious

They used to have a location in Los Angeles, which I loved and missed when it closed. So happy to see it reopened in Flushing. Same great food: Coffee & Curry. Great combo and really modern Malaysian.
Great food great customer service!!!!! Tried the tacos once now Iâ€™m hooked !!!!!
Had a wonderful time celebrating my birthday there! Yummy food!!

Great pizza! I recommend looking at the menu before you go. Seating is limited and you have to order before you can sit. We were rushed a bit to make sure our group could snag a seat.

Not a huge deal, just something to know!
I got a Kale Chicken Salad & a Turkey Club sandwich! (Pictured) The portions are amazing, and everything is cooked fresh!!! Please keep supporting small businesses!!!

It's okay. Messed up my daughter's order. Must not have heard what she said but also didn't verify what she asked for. $115 for 4 people. Add tip and it's up there. Not sure if it's actually worth that but we weren't disappointed, except for my daughter. We weren't amazed either.
Mango Habenero has become my favorite flavor
I personally really enjoyed this, I just got two chicken tacos. Simple and easy and nice and toasty. Iâ€™m happy with it, plus the guy at the counter was super sweet, so it really made it nice.
So good.
Very authentic sichuan and cantonese menu.  Friendly services to explain and introduce authentic dishes to new customers
Very good experience: good food, great ambiance and very courteous service.

Cafe Lago is a Seattle institution. We have been going there for almost 15 years. They are known for their feather light lasagna. I had their pea-mint-ricotta ravioli in a lemon cream sauce today, it was to die for. It is also a very kid friendly restaurant!
It was busy when we went, but orders seemed to be filled quickly.  The staff were super nice!

The robot at the drive thru is incompetent. It was not capable of understanding our order to the point that when we got to the window to pay the human had to advise they were out of mac n cheese and bo rounds. Do not like robot.

First of all, Their Fried Chicken on the Counter is Amazing ðŸ¤© Awesome. You must try it with the French fries which is great. But on the other hand, Their Louisiana Fried Rice is Horrible taste. This is nothing like Louisiana on their copy-cat cooking of that fried rice. Do not order fried rice. You will be disappointed. I give them 3 star for food. Their service is 5 star. There is no dine in over here. Itâ€™s take out all times.

We have loved Enrigos for a long time but - wow!  We went there for a belated birthday with some out of town guests last night and -(did I say) wow! The service was warm, welcoming, and simply better than any we've experienced anywhere.  They greeted us with wine, the appetizers were terrific, dinner was perfect. Smiles all the way around from everyone. It felt like such a special night. We'll be back.
Always good
I visit this Place when I come to Downtown...

Great visit, as always!  Betos never disappoints.. great food,  great service,  and a beautiful patio to enjoy this sunny Spring weather.  We had their awesome shrimp ceviche tower to start, along with a couple of delicious margaritas. The ceviche was full of tender,  flavorful shrimp, veggies,  and spicy sauce...amazing! For the entrÃ©e we shared the carnitas tacos...best carnitas in town!!
Service is always friendly and efficient.  We'll be back again and again... great job!!
Friendly server, great tasting roti. Relatively big portions. Flan was fantastic. 20% service charge that they are transparent about. Will definitely come again.
Dishonest server who added service charge for 2 pax.
I ate there yesterday. The food contains MSG it triggered vertigo so bad, I ended up in the hospital

Ruckus is always my go to place. After moving to Wake County 5-years ago, I discovered Ruckus during the Covid era. They had a spin the wheel promotion that lured me in. Iâ€™ve been a RUCKUS fan ever since. Their Pain Killers are magical and their food is always consistent. When the owner is in, he checks with every  customer to make sure the experience met expectations. During my dining experience last night, my server, Ryan ( Cary) greeted me with a jovial spirit and continued to update me about when my Ultimate Pizza would be ready. His positive attitude coupled with excellent service, consistently great food and quantity is why Ruckus remains my go to place.

Ordered delivery through Burger King app. Received order and was missing half of it (over $10 worth of food). Tried contacting customer support to get my money backâ€”they said theyâ€™re only able to offer a coupon. I donâ€™t want your coupon, Burger King. I want my money back for the food I did not receive. This is literally fraud.

It's among the best food we had while spending six days in New Orleans. Dining around 5:30 p.m. on a Wednesday in April, here's our experience.

1) Food: Everything we ate was delicious starting with the oysters and ending with the wagyu burger, which my seven-year-old daughter enjoyed too. The sunchokes are unique and worth ordering. My mother-in-law loved the squid ink pasta and my wife really enjoyed the buffalo tofu lettuce wraps (what they are known for).

2) Drink: Their menu includes cocktails, beer, wine, and more. I ordered a rainbow sherbet sour ale. My wife liked their brine drink for a savory option.

3) Service: From the hostess to the server, everyone was kind, efficient, and welcoming. Our food was perfectly timed.

4) Space: It's beautiful with a large indoor dining room and a bar. There are two unisex restrooms in the back near the stairs to the second level, which I assumed was for staff only.

5) Area: We found free street parking nearby. Located inside Bywater, it's a great neighborhood to walk around after dinner, finding little houses and parks. For dessert, we walked to nearby Big O's Original Popsicle Doorbell.

Nestled within the bustling confines of Washington, D.C.'s iconic Union Station, the Shake Shack outpost has firmly established itself as a must-visit dining destination for both commuters and tourists alike. As one of the nation's fastest-growing burger chains, Shake Shack has brought its signature blend of high-quality burgers, hot dogs, and frozen custard to this transportation hub, seamlessly integrating its vibrant, modern aesthetic into the station's historic architecture.

From the moment you step through the doors, the Shake Shack experience is defined by its warm, inviting atmosphere and attention to detail. The compact yet well-designed dining area features ample seating, both indoors and out, allowing patrons to enjoy their meals in comfort while taking in the bustling energy of the station around them. The clean, minimalist decor - complete with wood accents, subway tile, and the brand's signature neon signage - creates a sense of casual sophistication that perfectly complements the menu.

Of course, the real draw of this Shake Shack location is the food, and it certainly does not disappoint. The menu features all of the brand's signature items, from the classic ShackBurger, with its juicy beef patty and signature sauce, to the crispy, golden-brown crinkle-cut fries. But the real standouts are the Shake Shack-exclusive offerings, such as the Union Shack Burger, which pays homage to the location's iconic setting with a unique blend of toppings.

Beyond the standard fare, the Union Station Shake Shack also boasts an impressive selection of frozen custard concretes, shakes, and specialty beverages, catering to those with a sweet tooth or seeking a refreshing respite from their travels. The seasonal and limited-time offerings, in particular, have become highly anticipated and sought-after by the restaurant's loyal following.

What truly sets this Shake Shack location apart, however, is its seamless integration into the bustling Union Station environment. The restaurant's efficient layout and fast-casual service model make it an ideal option for commuters in a hurry, while its welcoming ambiance and commitment to quality also draw in leisure travelers and local patrons looking for a satisfying meal or snack. It's a perfect balance of convenience and culinary excellence.

Whether you're dashing to catch a train, exploring the nation's capital, or simply craving a delicious burger and fries, the Shake Shack at Union Station is sure to deliver a memorable dining experience that captures the vibrant energy and rich history of this iconic Washington, D.C. landmark.

If you live in Atlanta -- or visiting -- make time to reserve your spot at La Grotta, especially the outside patio. Vincent will escort you to a beautiful table where Brett will provide you with exemplary service. The outside patio is quiet and inviting with warm twinkle lights providing that coveted soft glow. La Grotta has just the right amount of fancy coupled with southern charm and an inviting team ready to provide you with top-notch service. The menu is amazing and has delicious options for those seeking traditional northern Italian fare. Huge shout out to Vincent and Brett for making our experience terrific.

I have been going to this takeout restaurant for over ten years now and I could not say enough good things about it. I get to enjoy the delicious flavors of Chinese food right from my own home. From the moment I opened my shrimp lo mien and sesame chicken, I was impressed by the inviting aromas that wafted from each dish.
The menu offered an extensive selection of classic Chinese dishes, ranging from General Tso's chicken to vegetable lo mein. Each item I ordered was bursting with flavor and cooked to perfection. The attention to detail in preparation was evident, with ingredients and a balance of flavors that made every bite a delightful experience.
The efficiency of the take-out service was commendable. My order was ready for pickup within the promised time, and the staff was friendly and accommodating.
Portion sizes were generous, ensuring that I had enough for a satisfying meal and leftovers for the next day. This value for money made the experience even more enjoyable.
Chinese take-out restaurants often serve as a convenient and reliable option, and this particular establishment did not disappoint. It delivered a delicious and hassle-free dining experience, making it an ideal choice for those looking to savor the flavors of Chinese cuisine without the need for a sit-down meal.

After years of trying, we finally coordinated the timing of a visit to New Orleans that allowed a reservation for lunch at Dooky Chase. It also coincided with a monster rain storm that saw crazy street flooding with 6 inches per hour falling from the sky and submerging the streets.
